headlines.description: — Darius Garland returned. The Cavaliers remain missing.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rozier's 29 lead Hornets over stumbling Cavaliers 119-98

headlines.description: — Malcolm Brogdon hung around until the finish and was the difference for the Indiana Pacers against Orlando.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brogdon helps Pacers rally late, beat Magic in OT 122-114

headlines.description: — James Harden saw the fake beards dangling from chins, oversized cutouts of his head waving above outstretched arms and heard 76ers fans shouting from the stands that they loved him.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden shines in Philly home debut with 26 points vs Knicks

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 37 points and Mike Conley scored nine points in overtime to help the Utah Jazz outlast the Houston Rockets 132-127 Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell, Conley lead Jazz to 132-127 OT win over Rockets

headlines.description: — Seemingly buried by the Miami Heat's avalanche of 3-point shots, the Milwaukee Bucks maintained their championship mentality and never gave up hope they could rally.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday's basket caps huge rally as Bucks stun Heat 120-119

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 33 points on 15-of-19 shooting and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Sacramento Kings 125-95 on Wednesday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brandon Ingram scores 33 points, Pelicans roll past Kings

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 29 points, Isaiah Roby added a career-high 26 and the injury-depleted Oklahoma City Thunder beat the heavily favored Denver Nuggets 119-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander, Roby lead Thunder by Nuggets, 119-107

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Even without their All-Star backcourt, the Phoenix Suns are a heavy load to handle.
headlines.shortLinkText: Suns rebound without Booker, Paul to rout Trail Blazers
